   1:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c **** /*
   2:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * Platform glue between Sensirion's SHDLC/streaming layer (unmodified,
   3:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * copied from the reference driver) and this project's own non-blocking
   4:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * UART peripheral driver (sx_uart.h).
   5:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *
   6:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * This file replaces v0's sensirion_uart_hal.c, which implemented these
   7:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * same functions using a dedicated FreeRTOS TX task plus busy-wait RX
   8:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * polling via bsp_delay_us(). This project is bare-metal (no RTOS), so
   9:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * that implementation cannot be reused as-is.
  10:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *
  11:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * Design note on blocking behavior:
  12:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * - sx_uart_write() calls HAL_UART_Transmit() directly, which is already
  13:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   blocking (up to 1000ms internal HAL timeout). sensirion_uart_hal_tx()
  14:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   therefore also blocks for the (very short, a few dozen bytes at
  15:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   9600-115200 baud) duration of the frame. This matches the reference
  16:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   driver's behavior and is acceptable because SPS30 commands are sent
  17:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   only occasionally (once per second at most in normal operation), not
  18:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   from a tight polling loop.
  19:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  * - sx_uart_read() does NOT block: it returns immediately with however
  20:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   many bytes are already queued (possibly zero), matching how gps.c
  21:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   already uses it elsewhere in this project. sensirion_uart_hal_rx()
  22:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   preserves that non-blocking behavior by doing a single read attempt
  23:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   and returning immediately. The retry/timeout loop that decides how
  24:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   long to keep waiting for a full SHDLC response already exists one
  25:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   layer up, in sensirion_streaming_shdlc.c's sensirion_shdlc_read_
  26:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   response() (see its "retries" / sensirion_uart_hal_sleep_usec loop) -
  27:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   this HAL layer must not duplicate that waiting logic, only provide
  28:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/sps30/sensirion_uart_hal.c ****  *   the raw non-blocking read primitive it polls against.
